AGI - The improvement of Pope Francis continues. At Casa Santa Marta the Pontiff continues with pharmacological therapy and respiratory and active motor physiotherapy. The Vatican press room refers to "significant improvements", also "on the resumption of the word".&nbsp;The situation from the medical point of view "is stationary", the "blood analysis performed last Wednesday, are in the norm". Moreover informed of the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-03-28/forte-terremoto-myanmar-tremano-anche-thailand-e-cina-30640883/"pertaining earthquake</a>, would have prayed for the affected populations of Myanmar and Thailand.
Another note of improvement, reduced use of high-flow oxygen. This type of oxygen supply, always through nasal cannulas, remains "only in part during the night". During the day the Pontiff, always uses the noses for oxygen but with a lighter dispensing, not at high flows.
The convalescence then goes on and despite Francis does not receive visits, maintains his "good mood". Moreover, it was already in the days of the shelter and it is even more once back home. The day spends between rest and prayer but also continues work "on documents that are transmitted to it by the various dicasteries of the Curia". This morning "the preaching of Lent at a distance" and concelebra put every day in the cap of Casa Santa Marta.&nbsp;
<h2> Angelus still written
For Sunday, it is expected that the text of the Angelus is only diffused, as already happened. On a hypothetical overlooking the window of the Apostolic Palace,» even a few minutes, on the example of last Sunday from the Gemini, still no indication from the Vatican. And always the press room of the Holy See states that "the problem is premature" also on the Pope's presence for Easter celebrations (the blessing Urbi et Orbi) or for the canonization of Carlo Acutis, scheduled for April 27. "It will be decided later on the basis of improvements," is the answer to those who asked if Francis' presence was indispensable from the canonical point of view.
