"She came to me with an olive branch," Mignini told me, "I didn't want to welcome her but then I accepted, I never had something like this: He wanted to talk to me face to face and I enjoyed his courage and his frankness. This girl is matured, she became wife and mother of two children."
&nbsp;
Amanda, now 37-year-old, wrote in her book 'Free' that Mignini did not admit to having wrong as she hoped but told her that she was not "the person who thought she was pursuing." "I came out of the trial in 2011 and cannot go back from a judicial statement," explained the ex pm, recalling that "in this process there was an immense media pressure".&nbsp;
