&nbsp;
The second serpent with his legs, instead, looks to the Sun, that is, contemplates the divine. While the last lizard >represents the power of Christ on evil >: it holds a scorpion in the mouth. And it's not over. Going on surprises continue. The first is a rosary sculpted by Bernini, > homage to the Virgin Mary to whom – we read in the texts dedicated to the work – the artist would have dedicated his entire masterpiece. While the second curiosity is seen lowering the look. On the bases of the Baldacchino are the faces of a woman with always different expressions, from labor to childbirth: is the cycle of Mater ecclesiae, the Church that puts the believer to the world. The architectural scenery ends with the wide curtain lying on the upper surface of the architecture. As is said in the Holy Scriptures, the tissue is re-evoking many things: He repaired the Jews during the exodus, recalls the Feast of Tabernacles, remembers the drapes of the Sancta sanctorum in Jerusalem and symbolizes the tent that Peter wanted to offer to the Master on Mount Tabor for the Festival of the Booths, near the Yom Kippur. I mean, it's a tribute.
